data.title: Phish
data.text:
Phish’s new studio album Evolve is now streaming everywhere you get your music, and in stores on LP and CD.

Phish will return to Mexico for its eighth Phish: Riviera Maya on January 29 thru February 1, 2025. Join us on the beach for four days and nights of sun, sand and Phish on Mexico’s beautiful Caribbean coast. Note that these 2025 dates are at the end of January, which is earlier than in previous

We are pleased to announce a number of Phish: Mondegreen updates, including Single Day Passes, Foundation Lounge details, shuttle service locations and a new GA Tent-Only Camping option, all of which go on sale this Thursday, June 6 at 12PM ET Details at https://mondegreen.phish.com. Evolve, Phish’s 16th studio album, drops July 12. It is available for pre-order now at Phish Dry Goods. The latest single from the album, “Oblivion”, is now streaming everywhere. Evolve was recorded in the fall of 2023 at the band’s Vermont recording studio The Barn, and was produced by Vance Powell and Bryce Goggin. True

Phish will embark on a 26-date Summer Tour (including their 4-day Mondegreen Festival) this July, August, and September. The Summer Tour begins July 19 with three shows in Mansfield, MA, and continues with multi-night runs in Uncasville, East Troy, St. Louis, Noblesville, Grand Rapids, and Bethel, culminating with the band’s annual Labor Day weekend tour

The Spectrum ‘97 is an all new 6-CD box set capturing two formative nights of Phish during their Fall Tour ‘97 apex, mixed from the band’s multitracks and mastered. It was recorded live 12/2-12/3/97 in Philadelphia, PA and celebrates a standout run across 33 songs and is available now.

We’re excited to announce The Spectrum ‘97, an all new 6-CD box set capturing two formative nights of Phish during their Fall Tour ‘97 apex, mixed from the band’s multitracks and mastered. The Spectrum ’97 was recorded live 12/2/97 and 12/3/97 at The Spectrum in Philadelphia, PA and celebrates a standout run across 33 songs

Round Room, Phish’s tenth studio album, is available on vinyl for the first time. It’s available now at Phish Dry Goods and in stores. Pick up the deluxe gatefold package, individually Foil-Numbered, with accordion fold insert, and 2-LPs pressed on 180g “Round Room” maroon/stone wax.
